    "description": [
        {
            "text": "Power is the rate at which work is performed or energy is transmitted, or the amount of energy required or expended for a given unit of time. As a rate of change of work done or the energy of a subsystem, power is: $P = W/t$, where $P$ is power, $W$ is work and {t} is time.",
